Name: glucokinase
Subsystem: Glycolysis, gluconeogenesis, galactose, starch, sucrose, amino sugar metabolism

Name: phosphoglucomutase
Notes: The enzyme also catalyses (more slowly) the interconversion of 1-phosphate and 6-phosphate isomers of many other alpha-D-hexoses, and the interconversion of alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate and 5-phosphate.

Name: glucose-6-phosphate isomerase
Notes: Also catalyses the anomerization of D-glucose 6-phosphate.

Name: fructose-1,6-bisphosphate aldolase
GPR: FbaC2 or Fba3 or FbaC5 or FbaC1

Name: glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase
GPR: GapC1 or GAPDH_3 or TPI/GapC3 or GapC4 or GapC2a

Name: pyruvate kinase
Notes: UTP, GTP, CTP, ITP and dATP can also act as donors. Also phosphorylates hydroxylamine and fluoride in the presence of CO2.

Name: dihydrolipoamide acetyl transferase
GPR: DHLTA_2 or DHLTA_1 mitochondria. DHLTA_3 or bd1828 cytoplasm.

Name: pyruvate carboxylase
Reaction: atp[m] + pyr[m] + hco3[m] -> adp[m] + pi[m] + oxaloacet[m]

Name: ATP-citrate synthase (ATP-citrate lyase)
Reaction: atp[m] + cit[m] + coa[m] <=> adp[m] + pi[m] + acca[m] + oxaloacet[m]
Notes: The enzyme can be dissociated into components, two of which are identical with EC 4.1.3.34 (citryl-CoA lyase) and EC 6.2.1.18 (citrate-CoA ligase).

Name: 2-oxoglutarate dehydrogenase E1 component (alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase)
Notes: Contains thiamine diphosphate. It is a component of the multienzyme 2-oxoglutarate dehydrogenase complex in which multiple copies of it dihydrolipoyllysine-residue succinyltransferase, which also binds multiple copies of EC 1.8.1.4, dihydrolipoyl dehydrog

Name: succinyl-coA synthetase (GDP-forming)
Reaction: gdp[m] + pi[m] + succoa[m] <=> gtp[m] + suc[m] + coa[m]
Notes: Itaconate can act instead of succinate, and ITP instead of GTP.

Name: succinyl-coa synthetase (ADP-forming)
Reaction: adp[m] + pi[m] + succoa[m] <=> atp[m] + suc[m] + coa[m]

Name: succinate dehydrogenase
Notes: A flavoprotein (FAD) containing iron-sulfur centres. The complex, present in mitochondria, can be degraded to form EC 1.3.99.1 succinate dehydrogenase, which no longer reacts with ubiquinone.

Name: malic enzyme (Oxaloacetate-decarboxylating) (NADP)
Reaction: mal[m] + nadp[m] <=> pyr[m] + co2[m] + nadph[m] + h[m]

Name: pyruvate-phosphate dikinase
Reaction: atp[p] + pyr[p] + pi[p] -> amp[p] + pep[p] + ppi[p]

Name: acetyl-coa carboxylase
Reaction: atp[p] + acca[p] + hco3[p] <=> adp[p] + pi[p] + mcoa[p]

Name: fructose-bisphosphatase
GPR: FBP or FBPC3(plastid) or FBPC2(plastid) or FBPC1(plastid) or FBPC4
